{"name": "better-abc", "metadata": {"name": "better-abc", "version": "0.0.3", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "home_page": "https://www.github.com/shonin/better-abc", "license": "BSD-3-Clause", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Python ABC plus abstract attributes", "upload_time": 1605048450}, "documentation": ["# Better ABC\n\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/23831510/abstract-attribute-not-property\n\n## Usage \n\n```python\nfrom better_abc import ABCMeta, abstract_attribute    # see below\n\nclass AbstractFoo(metaclass=ABCMeta):\n\n    @abstract_attribute\n    def bar(self):\n        pass\n\nclass Foo(AbstractFoo):\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.bar = 3\n\nclass BadFoo(AbstractFoo):\n    def __init__(self):\n        pass\n```\n\n```\nFoo()     # ok\nBadFoo()  # will raise: NotImplementedError: Can't instantiate abstract class BadFoo\n# with abstract attributes: bar\n```\n\nIf you want other features of ABC they need to be imported from the abc module directly.\n\n```python\nfrom abc import abstractmethod\nfrom better_abc import ABCMeta, abstract_attribute\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "better_abc", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "better_abc.abstract_attribute", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "better_abc.DummyAttribute", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "better_abc.ABCMeta", "bases": ["NativeABCMeta"], "methods": [{"name": "better_abc.ABCMeta.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "d